			<h2><a href="http://ardisragen.web.id/wordpress-for-your-business/" rel="bookmark">How to Use WordPress For Your Business Blog</a></h2>
			<div class="pmeta">02.07.2010 <span>&middot;</span> Posted in <a href="http://ardisragen.web.id/category/articles/" title="View all posts in Articles" rel="category tag">Articles</a>,  <a href="http://ardisragen.web.id/category/blog/" title="View all posts in Blog" rel="category tag">Blog</a></div>
			<div class="entry">
			  <div class="tweetmeme_button" style="float: right; margin-left: 10px;"><iframe src="http://api.tweetmeme.com/button.js?url=http%3A%2F%2Fardisragen.web.id%2Fwordpress-for-your-business%2F&amp;style=normal" height="61" width="50" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></div>
<div id="body" style="text-align: justify;">Are you consider to start business or working on expanding  an existing one, then you have probably thought about starting a blog ?. A  blog will gives you a dedicated outlet for talking about your business and  niche areas related to your field (business area). You can advertise your services,  write some thing about issues that are relevant to your area of interest, and  publish reviews of products that are of use to your blog readers.Â  As we know that <a href="http://ardisragen.web.id/category/wordpress/" target="_blank">WordPress</a> is one of the most commonly used blog platforms for business and personal blog in internet. This  is mainly because it is easy to use or user friendly and also endlessly customizable. If  you are starting a business blog you should use <strong>wordpress.org</strong> and  register your blog to a domain name related to your business or you can use hosting and install wordpress independent to get more WordPres features. Once  you&#8217;ve done, here I will share some tips for using WordPress as  your blog business<strong>.</strong></div>
<div style="text-align: justify;"><strong><br />
</strong></div>
<blockquote>
<div style="text-align: justify;"><strong>First</strong>, <em><strong>use good grammar and spelling</strong></em>. Yes,  the internet is a casual place. That means it is acceptable to use a  somewhat conversational tone when you write. However, you should keep in  mind that your blog is intended to be an asset to your business. That  means that it is important to keep it on a professional level.really that grammar and spelling will be increase your business credicilty. Part of  that is using good spelling and grammar. No matter how tempting it might  be, do not blog in textspeak or shorthand. Write like you talk, but  make sure that your blog is easy to read and understand while  maintaining a professional appearance.<span id="more-156"></span></div>
<div id="body" style="text-align: justify;">
<p><strong>Secondly<em>, be sure to credit  and cite any photographs that aren&#8217;t yours</em></strong>. This is something that many  people don&#8217;t realize, but pictures online aren&#8217;t just free for the  taking. You can&#8217;t just right click, hit save, and repost a picture. If  you see a picture online that you want to use, <strong>please ask the owner of the  picture for permission</strong>. You can do this via e-mail or by leaving a  comment on his or her blog. If you are looking for pictures that you can  use for free try Googling open source photography or free photos.</p>
<p><strong>Thirdly</strong>,<em><strong> do your best to engage your readers</strong></em>. Blogging is ultimately an  interactive medium. Part of the fun of having a website is building a  following and getting to know your regular readers. If you are trying to  get readers engaged, end your blog posts with a question and invite  people to answer in their comments. Besides encouraging people to  comment, many answers might give you ideas for future posts.</p>
<p><strong>Last  but certainly not least</strong>, <em><strong>make it easy for people to navigate your blog  or website</strong></em>. Use tags or keywords to identify blog posts by category. You  might also want to link current writing to previous posts on similar  topics. WordPress has a <a href="http://ardisragen.web.id/category/plugins/" target="_blank">plugin</a> called Similar Posts that will  automatically do this for you. This makes it easy for new readers to  find a multitude of information even if they come onto your blog looking  for something specific or may be you will need some<a href="http://ardisragen.web.id/category/seo/" target="_blank"> SEO tips</a> to increase your blog traffic.</div>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Blogging can be a great way to build your  business. By starting a WordPress blog you give yourself a dedicated  forum for talking about your field, your services, and topics of  interest. This enables you to build a following of people who are also  interested in your field of expertise. When you set yourself up as  someone who knows about a field people are more inclined to trust you  and become customers as well as readers.</p>
